posts.cooked:
Hello all Cheif Delphites!

I’m currently a member of FRC Team 93 and before kick-off we would like to share some of our best 3D printed electronics mounts for everyone to use this year whether that be for your radio, CANivore, or something more. Please look through this post and this thread and I can almost guarantee you’ll find something you like or might find at least a little nifty!

Radio Mounts - RadioHolderV6 (mounted with Nylock Nuts)

The CAN -hub for those who don’t fully get CAN -hub’s!!! This is a holder for these type of wire splicers that we occassionally used for a CAN -hub. Do I recommend this method of Star- CAN ? Not really… Do I have the CAD model for it? SURE DO!

Type of Splices we used - https://www.amazon.com/Wire-Connectors-Solderless-Stripping-Connection/dp/B07114RK67/ref=m_crc_dp_lf_d_t1_d_sccl_3_1/136-3655436-7288606?pd_rd_w=H8J66&content-id=amzn1.sym.76a0b561-a7b4-41dc-9467-a85a2fa27c1c&pf_rd_p=76a0b561-a7b4-41dc-9467-a85a2fa27c1c&pf_rd_r=XY31ZWSRD2GA55WF1QVR&pd_rd_wg=K9yIY&pd_rd_r=f0b2977c-4219-4bf3-97b4-b847c1536a42&pd_rd_i=B07114RK67&psc=1

It’s a hex adapter… Pretty much just what the file name is…

Google Drive file.

SDS Swerve Shield Elite Guard - We use SDS MK4 swerve drive modules (not MK4I just MK4) and we use swerve shields on said modules. This comes with 3 parts.The two large, main shields - A connection bracket that connects at the corner of the two large, main shields - And a handle piece for easier grip of said main shields. Some call it a cool project… I call it… the SDS Swerve Shield Elite Guard. Main shield -

Google Drive file.

Google Drive file.

Google Drive file.

Google Drive file.

SDS Swerve drive elite guard assembly Image 1216×1008 427 KB

SDS Swerve drive elite guard assembly Image 1216×1008 427 KB

SDS Swerve drive elite guard assembly Image 1216×1008 427 KB

I worked on this entire post for over 4 hours just compiling files and images so If there are any issues with the links not downloading please let me know! Also, if you want to remix any part or anything please by all means do so and some credit to our team is always appreciated. If there are any other issues with any part or something not working right please by all means contact me by responding to this thread and if there are any questions with parts I would be more than happy to answer them as the descriptions I put are not the most detailed… I would like to thank our previous VP of Engineering on Team 93 Spencer W. as a lot of these designs would not be what they are today without his help in previous seasons. Thanks again to the entire FRC and Chief Delphi community, and have a great kick-off!!! - Dom H. from Team 93
